**[Vorga's Decision to Stay and Defend]**

**GM** — *Vorga's military reasoning, pointing to the old orc*
> "She goes… So she goes… She's… she's now… she's now in a trustworthy moment, so what is it that she… she's, like… she looks at you and says. What, what, what do you, what, you know, do you want to make an ask for something, or…"

**Vukradin** — *offering to lead them home*
> "Well, I think we should, I mean, offer is to lead you back to your… To the old… to your old home."

**Wade Brown** — *objecting*
> "Well, we can't escort her right now, right? this from the Talosian, they'll be here."

**Vukradin** — *countering*
> "Why didn't leave now? Who cares?"

**Wade Brown** — *pushing back*
> "We don't want to deal with the incoming cults, the ritual coming."

**Vukradin** — *pressing the case*
> "Why would you want to risk these 20 non-combatants?"

**GM** — *Vorga's response*
> "She looks and goes, she goes, you cannot defend. She, she, she's very fixated on… she, like. Militarily speaking, 20 people in a forest being attacked by a group of… they don't have… you don't have enough people to come protect everyone."

**Vukradin** — *floating alternatives*
> "Brewbarry can carry everybody. Put everybody on brewberry's back, and we'll go really… and we got Boney, too."

**Wade Brown** — *adding*
> "And you can ride the elk, I can carry a couple."

**GM** — *Vorga's final reasoning*
> "cult summon creature today. We kill creature today, we go… we safely go to Icespire. We… creature kill… we know where creature come. Creature come here. We prepare defenses. We fight… we fight here. We go out, creature attacks where creature wants."

**GM** — *on the non-combatants*
> "She starts pointing at all the people around her. These… they don't move fast enough."

**Wade Brown** — *gallows humour*
> "Yeah, Granny Smith is slow."

